PERTH (miningweekly.com) &ndash; ASX-listed Lucapa Diamond Company has generated another A$1.25-million in revenue through the sale of 1 236 ct of diamonds from the Lulo mine, in Angola. Lucapa said on Monday that the latest parcel of diamond sales achieved an average price of A$1 013/ct. Lucapa has generated about A$20.3-million in revenue from diamond sales to date in 2017, averaging prices of about A$2 132/ct.